<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'About', page: 'about' }) %>

<main class="article-page">
  <article>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>About AI Credit News</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>
        <strong>AI Credit News</strong> is an automated news aggregation platform focused on the intersection
        of artificial intelligence and the financial services industry—specifically credit scoring, banking,
        lending, and related technologies.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        The world of AI in finance is evolving rapidly. New machine learning models are transforming how
        creditworthiness is assessed, how fraud is detected, and how banks serve their customers. Our mission
        is to make this complex landscape accessible to everyone—from industry professionals to curious learners.
      </p>

      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <p>
        We use a multi-stage process to curate relevant content:
      </p>
      <ol style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Automated Collection:</strong> Our system monitors RSS feeds from leading technology, finance, and banking publications.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>AI Filtering:</strong> Claude AI analyzes each article to determine its relevance to AI applications in credit and banking.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Categorization:</strong> Relevant articles are automatically categorized and tagged for easy discovery.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Summarization:</strong> AI-generated summaries make it easy to quickly understand each article's key points.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Categories We Cover</h2>
      <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>AI in Credit Scoring</strong> – Machine learning models for assessing creditworthiness</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Banking Automation</strong> – AI-powered banking operations and processes</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Fraud Detection</strong> – AI systems for detecting and preventing financial fraud</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Regulatory & Compliance</strong> – AI governance, fairness requirements, and regulations</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Risk Management</strong> – AI for financial risk assessment and mitigation</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Customer Experience</strong> – Chatbots, personalization, and AI interfaces</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Research & Innovation</strong> – Academic papers and new techniques</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Ethics & Bias</strong> – Fair lending, algorithmic bias, and responsible AI</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Difficulty Levels</h2>
      <p>
        Each article is assessed for technical difficulty:
      </p>
      <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><span class="difficulty-badge beginner">Beginner</span> – General audience, minimal jargon</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><span class="difficulty-badge intermediate">Intermediate</span> – Some technical knowledge helpful</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><span class="difficulty-badge advanced">Advanced</span> – Deep technical or domain expertise required</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <p>
        This platform is built with:
      </p>
      <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Node.js + Express.js backend</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">SQLite database</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Claude AI (Anthropic) for content analysis</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">RSS parsing for news collection</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS frontend</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        This is an automated news aggregation service. We do not create original content—we curate and
        summarize articles from other sources. All articles link to their original sources. The AI-generated
        summaries and categorizations are provided for convenience and may not be 100% accurate.
      </p>

      <p>
        <em>This platform does not provide financial advice. Always consult qualified professionals for
        financial decisions.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</main>

